exercise.name: Cat Camel
exercise.description: Start with your hands and knees on the ground.. Exhale as you reach the bottom of your sternum towards the ceiling.. To reverse, inhale as you arch your low back,, and finish by looking up..

exercise.name: Bird Dogs
exercise.description: Start on all fours. Keep your back flat, extend your left hand with your right foot then your right hand with your left foot

audios.text: Start on all fours. Keep your back flat, extend your left hand with your right foot then your right hand with your left foot

exercise.name: World's Greatest Stretch
exercise.description: Start in a high plank,, and step into a spiderman stretch.. Open up towards your front leg,, next rotate back,, to then straighten your front leg and stretch your hamstring.. Switch legs and repeat..

exercise.name: Arm Sweep Stretch
exercise.description: Laying on your right side with knees at 90 degrees, circle your left arm around the world and then tuck it behind your back.  Retrace the steps to get back to the starting position.

audios.text: Laying on your right side with knees at 90 degrees, circle your left arm around the world and then tuck it behind your back.  Retrace the steps to get back to the starting position.

exercise.name: Dead Bugs
exercise.description: Lie on your back with your legs up at ninety degrees and your arms extended straight up to the ceiling. Extend your right arm overhead and your left leg long. Repeat on the opposite side

exercise.name: Walkouts
exercise.description: Start tall with your arms overhead.. Hinge your hips back,, as you reach your arms down to the ground.. Walk your hands forward into a high plank,, pause, then reverse and stand back up..

exercise.name: Hip Cradles
exercise.description: Stand tall and gently pull your knee and ankle up toward your chest, stretching the outside of your hip.

exercise.name: Lateral Hip Openers
exercise.description: In a wide stance, slide side to side and push your hips back.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Front Raise
exercise.description: Standing in an athletic stance,, raise the dumbbells in front of you up to shoulder height.. Pause at the top before lowering under control.. Make sure to keep your arms straight,, and your core tight..

exercise.name: Dumbbell Lateral Shoulder Raises
exercise.description: From a standing position with dumbbells in front of your hips and a slight bend in your elbow. Raise both dumbbells out to the side under control until they get to shoulder height.  Lower back to the starting position.

audios.text: From a standing position with dumbbells in front of your hips and a slight bend in your elbow. Raise both dumbbells out to the side under control until they get to shoulder height.  Lower back to the starting position.

exercise.name: Dumbbell Bent Over Rear Delt Shoulder Raises
exercise.description: Hinge forward until your upper body is parallel with the ground. With the dumbbells starting beneath you and a slight bend in your elbow, raise both out to the side under control until they get to shoulder height.  Lower back to the starting position.
